2124→\section{w-contractible rings}
2125→
2126→\begin{definition}[w-contractible rings, {\cite[Definition 2.4.1]{proetale}}]
2127→    A ring \(A\) is \emph{w-contractible} if it is w-strictly local and $\pi_0(\spec{A})$
2128→    is extremally disconnected.
2129→    \label{def:w-contractible-ring}
2130→    \lean{IsWContractibleRing}
2131→    \leanok
2132→\end{definition}
2133→
2134→We will see that if a ring $A$ is w-contractible, every faithfully flat, ind-étale map $A \to B$ has a retraction. To show
2135→this we will perform a series of reductions.
2136→
2137→\begin{lemma}
2138→    \label{thm:ind-etale-plus-c-has-retraction-if-w-contractible}
2139→    \uses{def:w-contractible-ring,def:extremally-disconnected,def:ind-etale}
2140→    \lean{IsWContractibleRing.exists_retraction_of_zeroLocus_map_eq_closedPoints}
2141→    \leanok
2142→    Let $A$ be w-contractible and $I \subseteq A$ an ideal cutting out the set $X^c$ of closed points in $X = \spec{A}$.
2143→    Then every faithfully flat ind-étale map \(A \to B\) with \(B\) w-local and
2144→    whose closed points of \(\Spec (B)\) are exactly \(V(IB)\) has a retraction.
2145→\end{lemma}
2146→
2147→\begin{proof}
2148→  \uses{thm:ind-etale-base-change,thm:ind-etale-strictly-henselian-localization-isom,thm:ff-identifies-local-rings-plus-c-has-retraction-if}
2149→  Let \(A \to B\) be a faithfully flat ind-étale map with \(B\) w-local and such that the closed points of \(\Spec(B)\) are exactly \(V(IB)\). In this case, \(A \to B\) identifies local rings. To justify this, it suffices to check the condition at the maximal ideals of \(B\), which lie over maximal ideals of \(A\) since they map to \(V(I) = (\Spec(A))^c\). Since \(A\) is w-strictly local, the local rings of \(A\) at its maximal ideals are strictly Henselian.
